1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Science has a clearer story about the availability heuristic than social media does.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:13,200
The availability heuristic is about how we judge the likelihood of events based on how easily examples come to mind.

3
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:21,600
Think about it: if you hear more about plane crashes, you start thinking flying is dangerous, even if statistics say otherwise.

4
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:27,600
Studies show this bias affects decisions from health choices to politics, often leading us astray.

5
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:34,000
By recognizing this mental shortcut, we can make better decisions, relying on facts instead of feelings.

6
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,600
